 recycling service delivery energy storage and automotive industry experience combined with his sales and marketing knowledge has enabled him to conceptualize implement and deliver complex projects in particular he has been a leader in identifying and delivering market changing business models  chief financial officer lincoln greenidge lincoln greenidge is a canadian chartered professional accountant who has had various finance roles within industries such as commercial banking high technology life sciences dry food products and mining over the past two decades mr greenidge is the vp finance and corporate controller of enirgi group and the chief financial officer of leadfx inc prior to joining enirgi group he was corporate controller of hudbay minerals and iamgold leading the creation and development of their global finance teams  chief operating officer carlos galli carlos galli is an industrial engineer graduated from the school of engineering  university of buenos aires in  he has been working with ady resources a subsidiary of enirgi group since  first as industrial manager and then as general manager of operations mr galli has participated in the construction and management of a safe and sustainable lithium carbonate plant operation in the puna plateau of argentina which delivered product to  countries among his past work experiences he was an industrial segments manager in skf latin america and a process technology business manager in alfa laval among others  vice president investor relations and corporate communications jessica helm jessica helm has over a decade of experience in corporate communications and investor relations institutional trading and equity capital markets ms helm began her career in equity capital markets where she worked for macquarie bank and a leading independent investment dealer that was acquired by a large canadian bank prior to joining enirgi group in  jessica worked as an institutional equity sales trader at cibc world markets in toronto where she was responsible for executing trades of behalf of institutional clients jessica holds a bachelor of arts honours political science and honours applied studies and a specialization in international trade from the university of waterloo  vice president legal and corporate secretary darcy doherty d’arcy doherty is the vp legal and general counsel of enirgi group corporation and leadfx inc he is a former partner with gowling lafleur henderson llp now gowling wlg one of canada’s largest law firms where he worked with public mining companies focusing on corporate and securities law mr doherty holds a bachelor of arts from mcgill university a bachelor of laws from the university of victoria and a master of laws securities law from osgoode hall law school d’arcy is a member of the ontario bar home  contact  legal notice  subscribe to email alerts  copyright lsc lithium corporation powered by q inc  opens in new window lsc key statistics  lsc lithium corp financial ratios  marketwatch x tweet share this bulletin get news bulletins by email bulletin oil prices notch biggest oneday gain of the year » investor alert new york markets close in market snapshot winners and losers expand keep open close expand keep open close expand keep open close expand keep open close expand keep open close lsc lithium corp cve calsc go set alerts find a broker join td ameritrade market index overview news charts lsc lithium corp quotes are delayed by  min jul    am lsc quoteszigmandelayed   change   volume volume  quotes are delayed by  min quoteszigmandelayed previous close     change   day low day high    week low  week high   company description lsc lithium corp engages in the exploration activities it involves in the identification and evaluation of assets or a business for potential acquisition or participation in a business it currently operates a lithium brine projects such as salar rio grande tenements salar pastos grandes tenement lsc lithium corp engages in the explora